content.description: Start matched in a jug around the corner and work up the aretes.
content.location: Follow the cliffband past Carcass for about a minute. This climb faces west.

content.description: Start matched in the horizontal crack underneath the roof. A few powerful moves lead to a tall slab.
content.location: Follow the cliff band past Carcass for about a minute while looking downhill. You can't miss it.

content.description: Start left hand on ledge and right hand on arete. Slap up arete and topout.
content.location: 10 feet directly to the right of Charlize Heron.

content.description: Start right hand on arete and left on a jug in the face. Climb straight up the overhang by compressing. A spotter would be good for the top.
content.location: On large boulder facing downhill in the talus under Vulture Lookout West.

content.description: Start with a right hand side-pull and left hand on the arete. A few powerful compression moves lead up the face. Detached blocks are not used.
content.location: Located on the backside of The Verdant Wilds boulder.

content.description: Start matched on large undercling and climb up double arete feature to the lip.
content.location: Right side of Vulture Lookout West when looking down hill.

content.description: Start in obvious pockets. Make two dynamic moves to the lip.
content.location: 20 feet west of Atari Dream in the Vulture Lookout talus field.

content.description: From a sit with a sidepull feature under the roof and a sidepull with the right hand, climb the Boulder.
content.location: If at the lookout this is 200 feet below and slightly left.  At same level as carcass, fledgling, pidgeon pole and just below Barn Swallow.

content.description: Start with a low right hand edge and a left hand jug at about head height. Interesting moves lead up the gently overhanging feature.
content.location: Downhill from "The Verdant Wilds"

content.description: Climb fun easy boulder to a really cool top-out.
content.location: About 10 feet right of Empty Nest

content.description: Climb up boulder to a cool and committing top-out
content.location: Backside of Learning to Fly boulder.  About 10 feet east of Empty Nest.

content.description: Start low on left slot and good right hold and lock off to hit the funky crimp.  Work your way up face and top out.
content.location: Directly below Electric Sky at the top of the talus field.

content.description: Low start to Electric Sky. Start at the base of the small gulley on a jug. Climb a series of relatively easy, yet taxing moves into the start of Electric Sky and top out as for that boulder.
content.protection: 5-6 pads and spotter for the top out.
content.location: Same as Electric Sky. To the right of the overlook, if standing on the overlook looking down at the talus field.

content.description: Climb the tall slab, avoiding detached blocks.
content.location: To the right of Carcass.

content.description: Start on large right hand side-pull feature and small left hand. Work through the bulge.
content.location: Vulture Lookout main wall.

content.description: From a sit on the slabby side of the arete, balance and squeeze up, transferring left to the overhanging side at 2/3rds height and finish it.  A little dabby and not the best landing but a long and fun problem.
content.location: On a large Boulder and facing down hill.  If looking from the lookout it is 150/200 feet downhill and slightly west.  The problem Carcass is 50 feet west.

content.description: Start sitting with right hand undercling/sidepull and left on a pinch. Climb up arete.
content.location: Next to Freebie on the right side of the Talus.

content.description: Start low on good ledge climb up and right through roof and climb up jugs on the face. V1 variation - Climb the direct straight up though triangle feature directly above start and quest up the face.
content.location: 20 feet right of Murder.

content.description: Start sitting with a jug for the left hand and a bad, slopey undercling for the right.  Bust a big move for the right hand and finish it up.  Next to Loon Song.
content.location: If at the lookout this is 200 feet below and slightly left.  At same level as carcass, fledgling, pidgeon pole and just below Barn Swallow.

content.description: Obvious start on ledge and goes up to a good right hand gaston.  Tops out direct.
content.location: To the right (east) of Carrion by about 20 feet.

climbs.name: Emperor Penguin
climbs.fa: Ian CB, Kevin Baker, Eggert probably

content.description: From an obvious left facing sidepull climb the face through sidepulls and utilizing the arete higher.  A longer pull to the lip, mantle and boom, you’re standing on the lookout.  No detached blocks are used.
content.protection: More pads and a spotter is safer.  Four is pretty good. Don’t barndoor off into the talus.
content.location: If standing on the lookout and looking out it is on your left and tops out where you may be standing.  Just around the corner from Bald Eagle.

climbs.name: Electric Sky
climbs.fa: Probably Ian CB and Ben Strobel

content.description: From a sit with good low holds climb through the lightning boltesque feature to an engaging mantle.  A spot and a few pads are nice.  Get on it!
content.location: When at the lookout and looking out this is 40 feet or so to the right and climbs the cliff line that makes the lookout.  You can see the problem from above.

content.description: Start sitting with a slopey right hand and a faint gaston for the left.  Climb the slab, gaining a good edge for the right hand and a pocket for the left.  A long move to the next break and an easing finish follows.
content.location: If looking out from the lookout this is on the left by 40 feet.  It climbs the cliff that forms the lookout.

content.description: Start from a crouch with a pockety hold for the right hand and an edge for the left.  Climb through the center of the pillar feature, gaining an undercling, a huge foothold, and pop for the lip.  A left version goes at V3, a right about V2.
content.location: If standing on the lookout and looking out, this is on the left by forty feet.  It climbs the cliffline that forms the look out.

content.description: Start matched on good ledge, climbing up through a great pinch and edges.
content.location: 75 yards directly west of Fledgling.

content.description: Start under roof with left hand on block pinch and right on sloping side-pull under a notch.
content.location: On the right side on the talus downhill of the lookout, directly east of Pigeon Post.

content.description: If you are standing at the lookout this probably tops out right where you are. Start sitting with sidepulls.  Move through a sidepull and a slopey ledge and finish up the airy arete.  And you are back on the lookout.
content.location: Tops out on the lookout.

content.description: Start right hand on notch of the right arete, left on blocky pinch. Climb straight up the double aretes compressing to the lip. A fall at the top would be dangerous.
content.location: On large pillar in the middle of Vulture Lookout West.

content.description: Low start on good jugs and work up and around the left (west) arete.
content.protection: Pads. Try not to fall near the top.
content.location: In the talus field next to Vulture Lookout. Easiest access is from above via the CCC trail. See picture for location.

content.description: Sunny and a very nice collection of high quality and fun boulder problems close to each other.  Some of the lines are highball but not all.  There is plenty of potential for new lines to be had.
